This paper focuses on material recognition during robotic manipulation, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. The use of spectroscopy for material recognition involves analyzing spectral data, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.AI, cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a neural network model for material classification, which is a common technique in information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
